{"id":200544,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impresario","text":"An Impresario is somebody who organizes concerts, operas, ballets or plays. The word comes from the Italian word \"impresa,\" which means \"an enterprise\" or \"undertaking\".\nSome very famous impresarios from the past include Rudolf Bing, Sergei Diaghilev, Richard D'Oyly Carte, Fortune Gallo, and Sol Hurok.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Concert","surface_form":"concert","offset":40},{"uri":"Opera","surface_form":"opera","offset":50},{"uri":"Ballet","surface_form":"ballet","offset":58},{"uri":"Play_(theatre)","surface_form":"plays","offset":69},{"uri":"Italian_language","surface_form":"Italian","offset":100},{"uri":"Rudolf_Bing","surface_form":"Rudolf Bing","offset":221},{"uri":"Sergei_Diaghilev","surface_form":"Sergei Diaghilev","offset":234},{"uri":"Richard_D%27Oyly_Carte","surface_form":"Richard D'Oyly Carte","offset":252},{"uri":"Fortune_Gallo","surface_form":"Fortune Gallo","offset":274},{"uri":"Sol_Hurok","surface_form":"Sol Hurok","offset":293}]}